com.k2.Expressions.expression

Class AbstractExpression<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.k2.Expressions.expression.AbstractExpression<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value returned by the expression
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Expression<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractPredicate, ExprAbsolute, ExprAs, ExprConcatenate, ExprCurrentDate, ExprCurrentTime, ExprCurrentTimestamp, ExprDifference, ExprLength, ExprLiteral, ExprLocate, ExprLower, ExprMod, ExprNeg, ExprNullIf, ExprNullLiteral, ExprProd, ExprQuot, ExprSqrt, ExprSubstring, ExprToBigDecimal, ExprToBigInteger, ExprToBoolean, ExprToDate, ExprToDouble, ExprToFloat, ExprToInteger, ExprToLong, ExprToString, ExprTrim, ExprUpper, GetterExpression, ParameterExpression

    public abstract class AbstractExpression<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Expression<T>
    This abstract class forms the basis of the Expression classes This class implemnts the hashCode() and equals(Object) methods using the name of the java type returned by the expression and the alias value returned by the getAlias() method. Consequently expressions are considered equal if their implementing classes are equal and they return the same data type and their getAlias() methods return the same value.
    Author:
    simon
